INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3200','letter','1778-06-15','Artillery Park','RI','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','In all considerable armies in Europe, a General Officer has the command and direction of the artillery, and the preparation of every thing pertaining to the ordnance department','ltr_hek3200.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume II., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3700','letter','1781-03-27','New Windsor','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','There being no established principles to govern the appointments to the vacancies of officers in the artillery, some doubts have arisen since the last regulation of the army, whether the right of appointment is in Congress','ltr_hek3700.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3701','letter','1781-07-02','Peekskill','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','If your Excellency should think fit to alter the time of the arrival of the stores from Philadelphia, I pray you to write to the Board of War on the subject.','ltr_hek3701.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3702','letter','1781-02-07','New Windsor','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','I proceeded to the States of Connecticut, Rhode Island, Massachusetts, and New Hampshire, and delivered the despatches, with which I was charged, to the Governors and to the President, to whom they were addressed.','ltr_hek3702.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume III., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3000','letter','1775-12-05','Fort George','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','I arrived here yesterday, and made preparation to go over the Lake this morning, but General Schuyler reaching here before day, prevents my going over for an hour or two.','ltr_hek3000.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3001','letter','1775-12-17','Fort George','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','I returned from Ticonderoga to this place on the 15th instant, and brought with me the cannon, &c.; it having taken nearly the time I conjectured it would to transport them here.','ltr_hek3001.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek3002','letter','1777-06-05','Middlebrook','NJ','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','A resolution, of the 30th ultimo, has been shown to me by some French officers attached to the corps of artillery under my command, ordaining that all officers of artillery, ... shall take rank, in the American artillery, according to the dates of th','ltr_hek3002.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume I., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4300','letter','1784-02-21','Boston','MA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','Your calm retreat of Mount Vernon must be a source of ineffable delight to you. You can from thence take a retrospective view of the critical exigencies of the war, and see a thousand ways by which the issue might have been the reverse of what it is.','ltr_hek4300.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4301','letter','1784-05-28','Annapolis','MD','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have now been here nearly one week, and nothing of importance has been decided upon, owing to the contrariety of sentiments concerning the powers vested in Congress to raise troops, in time of peace, for any purpose.','ltr_hek4301.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4302','letter','1785-03-24','Boston','MA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','My jealousy for your fame is so high that I should prefer seeing you, Cincinnatus-like, following your plough, rather than accept the least pecuniary reward whatever.','ltr_hek4302.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4303','letter','1787-01-14','New York','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','With respect to the Convention proposed to meet in May, there are different sentiments. Some suppose it an irregular assembly, unauthorized by the Confederation, which points out the mode by which any alterations shall be made.','ltr_hek4303.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4304','letter','1787-08-14','New York','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','I have hitherto forborne the pleasure, my dear Sir, of writing to you since my return from Philadelphia. I have been apprehensive, that the stages of the business of the Convention might leak out, and be made an ill use of by some people.','ltr_hek4304.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4305','letter','1787-10-03','New York','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','The new Constitution is received with great joy by all the commercial part of the community.','ltr_hek4305.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4306','letter','1788-07-28','New York','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','It is with the most sincere satisfaction that I congratulate you on the unconditional adoption of the Constitution by the Convention of this State.','ltr_hek4306.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4307','letter','1788-12-21','New York','NY','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','In the States of New Hampshire, Massachusetts, and Connecticut, the great object of organizing the new Constitution, engrosses the attention of the people. It is with sincere satisfaction that I can assert, from personal observation, that the affecti','ltr_hek4307.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4308','letter','1790-02-15','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','The serious crisis of affairs in which the United States are involved with the Creeks, requires that every honorable and probable expedient that can be devised should be used to avert a war with that tribe.','ltr_hek4308.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4309','letter','1791-04-10','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','By the information from Fort Harmar, of the 17th, and Pittsburg, of the 31st, it would appear that the Delawares and Wyandots are committing depredations, and that they will be joined in the war against us.','ltr_hek4309.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4310','letter','1791-06-08','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','Colonel Procter has just arrived in this city by the way of Fort Pitt. He was unable to go forward to the western Indians without an escort of the Six Nations.','ltr_hek4310.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4311','letter','1791-09-22','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','The Minister of France has written me a letter, of which the inclosed is a copy.','ltr_hek4311.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4312','letter','1792-07-28','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','A meeting of the Cherokees, at Estanaula, had taken place, which lasted from the 24th of June to the 1st of July, at which the Little Turkey and many other Chiefs were present','ltr_hek4312.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4313','letter','1792-08-05','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','General Putnam, in his letter of the 5th of July, which principally contains the same information as that mentioned in Wilkinson\'s letters, states it as his opinion, that a treaty ought to be concluded, as soon as possible, with the Wabash Indians','ltr_hek4313.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4314','letter','1792-08-31','Philadelphia','PA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','The manner of treating the Spaniards and McGillivray, was unanimously considered as the most proper to be adopted in the present conjuncture.','ltr_hek4314.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4315','letter','1794-03-19','','','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','As it is understood that the bill for fortifying the ports and harbours has passed into a law, I beg leave respectfully to lay before you the following thoughts upon the manner of executing this business.','ltr_hek4315.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4316','letter','1796-01-28','Boston','MA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','Mr. Adams, the Governor, may console himself with his good intentions, but he has no credit for them in the opinion of the wise and enlightened part of his countrymen.','ltr_hek4316.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
INSERT INTO media VALUES ('ltr_hek4317','letter','1797-01-15','Boston','MA','US','Henry','Knox','','George','Washington','','individual','','The loss of two lovely children, on which you condoled in that letter, has been recently revived and increased by the death of our son, of seven years of age, bearing your name.','ltr_hek4317.txt','hans.brough@yahoo.com',NULL,20090802183836,NULL,'Correspondence of the American Revolution; Being Letters of Eminent Men to George Washington, from the Time of His Taking Command of the Army to the End of His Presidency, Volume IV., Jared Sparks, 1853',0);
